```
using System.Numerics;

R<float> r = default;
r.GetScaled<float>(V<int>.Zero, V<float>.Zero); // This doesn't match any overload and should be an error.

struct V<T> where T : INumberBase<T>
{
    public static V<T> Zero = default;
}

struct B<T> where T : INumber<T>
{
}

struct R<T> where T : INumber<T>
{
}

static class B
{
    extension<TSelf>(B<TSelf> b)
        where TSelf : INumber<TSelf>
    {
        public B<TSelf> GetScaled(V<TSelf> scale, V<TSelf> anchor) => default;
    }
}

static class R
{
    extension<TSelf>(R<TSelf> r)
        where TSelf : INumber<TSelf>
    {
        public R<TSelf> GetScaled(V<TSelf> scale, V<TSelf> anchor) => default;
    }
}
```

**Diagnostic Id**:

CS1929 and CS1503

**Expected Behavior**:

The error message should consider the available overloads' receiver types before deciding what the "best" overload was.  The error should read:

`CS1503: Argument 2: cannot convert from 'V<int>' to 'V<float>'`

**Actual Behavior**:

In this case, an incorrect explanation of the error is given to the user.

`CS1929: 'R<float>' does not contain a definition for 'GetScaled' and the best extension method overload 'B.extension<float>(B<float>).GetScaled(V<float>, V<float>)' requires a receiver of type 'B<float>'`

`AddOtlpExporter` was unconditionally registered for both the metrics and tracer providers, sending data even when no OTLP endpoint is configured or expected.

## Changes

- **`EnvironmentVariableNames.cs`** – Added `DOTNET_CLI_TELEMETRY_ENABLE_EXPORTER` constant (value: `DOTNET_CLI_TELEMETRY_ENABLE_EXPORTER`).
- **`TelemetryClient.cs`** – Added static field `s_enableOtlpExporter` (defaults `false`); both `AddOtlpExporter()` calls (metrics + tracer) are now gated behind it.

```csharp
// Only active when DOTNET_CLI_TELEMETRY_ENABLE_EXPORTER=true
if (s_enableOtlpExporter)
{
    s_metricsProviderBuilder.AddOtlpExporter();
    // ...
    s_tracerProviderBuilder.AddOtlpExporter();
}
```

The OTLP exporter is **off by default**. Set `DOTNET_CLI_TELEMETRY_ENABLE_EXPORTER=true` (or `1`/`yes`) to re-enable it. A follow-up can add auto-detection of a listening OTLP endpoint.
